The paper deals with coded caching and video delivery, which are topics related to information theory and networking. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also considers the popularity of video files and audience retention rates, which are related to multimedia (cs.MM) and distributed computing (cs.DC). Finally, the paper proposes a decentralized scheme, which can be related to social and information networks (cs.SI).
